wikipedia_page.main: Edmund Beckett Faber, 1st Baron Faber (9 February 1847 – 17 September 1920) was a British Conservative politician.

response: Faber was the second surviving son of Charles Wilson Faber (1813–1878) a director of the Great Northern RailwayCharles Wilson Faber and the nephew of Lord Grimthorpe. He was the brother of Edmund Faber, 1st Baron Faber, and of Mrs Edward Kennard (1850–1936), a novelist.
